radiographic_examinations.findings: Small amount of right pleural effusion most likely is a sequela of substantial ascites. The aorta and pulmonary arteries are unchanged, coronary calcifications are extensive and unchanged. No mediastinal, hilar or axillary lymphadenopathy; airways are patent; no lytic or sclerotic lesions. Hemangioma in T3 is present, unchanged. No pulmonary nodules, masses or consolidations to suggest metastatic disease.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Small amount of right pleural effusion is new since the previous examination.
